data.text:
The Dollar/TL is trading at the level of 34.04.

The USD/TRY is trading at 34.04 level after starting the day with an increase. Yesterday, the USD/TRY moved within a narrow range and ended the day at 34.0200 with a 0.08% increase compared to the previous closing. After starting the new day with an increase, the USD/TRY is currently trading at 34.0430 with a 0.10% increase compared to the previous closing as of 10:30 am.

5 minutes ago...

The first three were dominated by banks! Here are the top 100 companies paying the most taxes in 2023.

The tax top earners of the year 2023 have been announced. Sel√ßuk Bayraktar, the Chairman of Baykar, was the highest taxpayer in Turkey last year, followed by Haluk Bayraktar in second place. The top 100 companies that paid the most corporate tax were also announced. Banks made up the first 8 of the list. Ziraat Bank ranked first, Garanti Bank ranked second, and Akbank ranked third.

15 minutes ago...

A mouse head came out of the seed package bought from the chain supermarket.

Two young people who bought sunflower seeds from a chain supermarket were astonished when they opened the package and found an incredible thing. The mouse head that came out of the sunflower seed package sold with the label "Award-Winning" in supermarkets surprised the young people.

25 minutes ago...

More than 200 people were killed in an attack by Al-Qaeda affiliated groups in a village in Burkina Faso.

At least 100 villagers and soldiers lost their lives in an attack organized by Al-Qaeda-affiliated groups in a village in Burkina Faso. Experts in the region have described this attack as one of the deadliest attacks of the year. Al-Qaeda claimed responsibility for the attack and stated that they had gained "full control over a militia position" in Barsalogho, a strategic town in Kaya. The Minister of Security of Burkina Faso announced that the government responded to the attack by providing support both on the ground and in the air.

35 minutes ago...

Chickenpox is spreading rapidly! The number of cases and deaths has reached alarming levels.

The monkeypox outbreak that has alarmed the world has now spread to African countries. A total of 22,863 cases and 622 deaths have been reported in 13 African Union member countries.

-15 minutes ago...
